com.noctarius.borabora.builder.encoder

Interface SequenceBuilder<B>

  • Type Parameters:
    B - the parent builder's type
    All Superinterfaces:
    ValueBuilder<SequenceBuilder<B>>

    public interface SequenceBuilder<B>
extends ValueBuilder<SequenceBuilder<B>>
    The SequenceBuilder interface is used to create sequence (array) elements in the generated CBOR stream. A SequenceBuilder instance is retrieved by calling ValueBuilder.putSequence() ()} or ValueBuilder.putSequence(long) for either an indefinite or fixed size sequence.

    • Method Detail

      • endSequence

        B endSequence()
        Ends the current sequence. In case of an indefinite sequence, it will also write the closing tag to the generated CBOR stream. In case of a fixed size sequence, the number of created elements is tested and if the number is less than the configured number of elements expected, an IllegalStateException is thrown.
        Returns:
        the parent builder
